  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The fourth floor stairs led up a small hill of steps toward a quiet hallway with a low ceiling.",
      "zh": "四樓的樓梯往上通往一小段階梯，通向一條天花板很低、很安靜的走廊。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco noticed the stairs were neither too high nor too steep, just an ordinary set of steps like any other.",
      "zh": "Coco 注意到那座樓梯既不會太高也不會太陡，就跟其他樓梯一樣普通。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The newest note in the Friday Box was also the strangest one yet: no question, just two short sentences.",
      "zh": "星期五箱子裡最新的這張紙條，也是目前為止最奇怪的一張：沒有問題，只有兩句短短的話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Nobody uses the fourth floor stairs,\" it said. \"And nobody says why.\"",
      "zh": "紙條上寫著：「沒有人會用四樓的樓梯，也沒有人說為什麼。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice had walked past those stairs a hundred times without really looking at them.",
      "zh": "Bernice 已經走過那座樓梯上百次，卻從來沒有真正看過它。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When she finally stopped to look, she understood the note immediately.",
      "zh": "當她終於停下來看的時候，她馬上就懂了那張紙條的意思。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The stairs looked completely normal, but every student walking by used the other staircase instead.",
      "zh": "那座樓梯看起來完全正常，但每個經過的學生都寧願繞去用另一座樓梯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Maybe it's closed,\" Coco said. But it wasn't. No sign, no rope, nothing stopping anyone.",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「也許它是關閉的。」但並沒有，沒有告示，沒有繩子，沒有任何東西擋著。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They asked the first classmate they saw. \"I just don't use them,\" she said. \"Everyone knows not to.\"",
      "zh": "他們問了第一個遇到的同學：「我就是不用那座樓梯，」她說：「大家都知道不要用。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Knows what, exactly?\" Bernice asked.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「大家到底知道什麼？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The student thought for a moment. \"Someone got hurt there. A long time ago. That's what I heard.\"",
      "zh": "那個學生想了一下：「有人在那裡受過傷，很久以前的事了，我是聽說的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "A second student told a similar story, but with different details: a different year, a different kind of accident.",
      "zh": "第二個學生講了一個類似的故事，但細節不一樣：不同的年份，不同種類的意外。"
    },
    {
      "en": "A third student had heard it happened at night. A fourth said it happened during a school trip, which made no sense at all.",
      "zh": "第三個學生聽說那件事發生在晚上，第四個學生說是在校外教學時發生的，這根本說不通。"
    },
    {
